description:
The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree International Equity Index.
 At least 95% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is a fundamentally weighted index that is comprised of dividend-paying companies in the industrialized world, excluding Canada and the United States, that pay regular cash dividends. It is non-diversified.
